                <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Calius <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Cla</abbr><ex>udia</ex></expan> Cremona <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/>Concordia decurio quaes<supplied reason="lost">tor</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="3"/>operis publicis in Bithynia fuit <supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Calio <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>Cla</abbr><ex>udia</ex></expan> Cremona Malliolo fratri <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="5"/>et in operis publicis in Asia et <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Y: Zwischen 42 und 40 v.Chr.: Concordia wird colonia. (B): CIL: Abweichungen in Lesung und Ergänzung. Nach CIL V 8666 = ILS 1468 von Inschrift auf rechter Seite noch mehr erhalten (durch Abschrift aus dem 16. Jh. überliefert): Z. 1: Na[talis]; Z. 2: quaestor; Z. 3 is tes[tamento]; Z. 4: is fo[---]; Z. 5: Isau[ria].</p>
            </div>
